</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD0368C707EFF8FFF16854E322FFA45" blockId="6.[140,1108,1363,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">
This species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D0F707EFF8FFD84854E3396F9C9" authority="Bernhauer, 1909" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1909" box="[542,971,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subpygmaea">
<emphasis id="B91BEA9E707EFF8FFD84854E335BF9C9" box="[542,774,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">Acrotona subpygmaea</emphasis>
Bernhauer, 1909
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B7D707EFF8FFC6F854E30BAF9EC" author="Gusarov VI" pageId="6" pageNumber="273" refId="ref7585" refString="Gusarov VI (2003 c) A catalogue of the athetine species of American north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Athetini). http: // nhm. ku. edu / ksem / peet / catalogs / cataweb. htm [accessed 1. II. 2009]" type="url" year="2003">Gusarov (2003c)</bibRefCitation>
, however, the two 
<typeStatus id="54D4882E707EFF8FFE5B85A331ACF9EC" box="[449,497,1434,1460]" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D0F707EFF8FFD0F85A3336BF9EC" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1909" box="[661,822,1434,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subpygmaea">
<emphasis id="B91BEA9E707EFF8FFD0F85A3336BF9EC" box="[661,822,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">A. subpygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the median lobe of the aedeagus missing in the male and a collapsed spermatheca in the female, complicating taxonomic evaluation. Majka et al. (2008), however, revalidated the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D0F707EFF8FFB9E85D83409F9A2" baseAuthorityName="Casey" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1028,1108,1505,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avia">
<emphasis id="B91BEA9E707EFF8FFB9E85D83409F9A2" box="[1028,1108,1505,1531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">A. avia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and reported the species from 
<collectingRegion id="49ABF86E707EFF8FFE78863D3233FA45" box="[482,622,1539,1566]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="6" pageNumber="273">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
